Project Title: Remote Deposit Capture Project
Project Justification: Several banks are offering a new service that allows customers to scan their checks via a special scanner that they can own and a bank account to deposit them. Blue Bank wants to remain on the cutting edge by providing this service that can save both the customer and the bank time and money over the traditional ATM or cashier deposit systems.
Project Characteristics and Requirements:
1.     Budget: $500,000
2.     Time limit: 6 months
3.     Website has technical support
a.     Annual budget of $150,000
4.     Project Steering comittee includes:
a.     VP of IT, Harold Johnson (project sponsor)
b.    VP of Marketing, Tricia Young
5.     Team
a.     Internal
                                          i.	Myself (project manager)
                                         ii.	Mike and Sophie (IT Department)
                                        iii.	Carlos and Joanna (marketing)
                                        iv.	John Purchasing Department)
b.    External
                                          i.	Christian (Code Corp)
                                         ii.	Alexandra (DevAn
6.     System needs to be reliable, secure and easy to use
7.     System needs to be integrated with the current blue Bank website
8.     Online instructions and technical support needs to be provided (project will develop the system for the first year)
9.     Scanners need to be purchasable online and at local Blue Bank locations
10.  Marketing campaign needs to be planned and launch
11.  Everything needs to be thoroughly tested
Summary of Project Deliverables
Project management-related deliverables: Business case, charter, team contract, scope statement, WBS, schedule, cost baseline, status reports, final project presentation, project report, lessons-learned report, and any other documents required to manage the project.
Product-related deliverables:
1.     Integrated online system that allows users to purchase scanners, scan and deposit their checks remotely, and get technical support on the system: The online system will need to be friendly for all users and user studies will be necessary to verify this. The depositing will need to be very secure as to ensure no one will have access to steal documents. This will include one person providing online support 24-7 all year.
2.     Phone system that allows customers to reach technical support: instructions and a database of knowledge for handling support cases. This will include two phone service people working 24-7 all year.
3.     A selected scanner that is available at various store locations: this will need to be inexpensive for customers, but also robust and easy to use
4.     A launched marketing campaign for the effort: This could be either or both a traditional marketing campaign launched via local branches, radio services, television services and scanner giveaways or an online campaign. Four marketing people will be working full time on this campaign for the first six months.
Project Success Criteria
The goal is to complete the project within six months for no more than $500,000. Following the initialization of the project, we want to have the support team successfully in place and costing no more than $150,000 for a full year. We need to also be able to measure the benefits of this system and meet a goal of $400,000 in benefits per year. The site needs to be user friendly and a user adoption rate goal should be developed and met.

SCOPE STATEMENT
Project Title: Coding Blitz Competition Website
Project Justification: This project intends to further a bond between ICS instructors and students, while offering a fun outlet to encourage casual coding among students. It also intends to further knowledge of students and provide incentive for participation in the ICS community.
Project Characteristics and Requirements:
1.     Budget: $500
2.     Time limit: 43 days
3.     Website up and running with functioning weekly competitions
a.     Requires participation of an ICS instructor
4.     Project Steering comittee includes:
a.    Grant Arjani (Project Coordinator)
5.     Team
a.     Internal
                                          i.	Grant Arjani (Project Coordinator)
                                         ii.	Mike and Sophie (Project Secretary)
                                        iii.	Carlos and Joanna (Project Designer)
                                        iv.	John (Research Analyst)
			     v.	Matan Lurey (Project Manager)
6.     System needs to be reliable, secure and easy to use
7.     System needs to be integrated with the current ICS website.
8.     Online instructions and technical support needs to be provided.
9.  Marketing campaign needs to be planned and launch with the help of ICS student organizations
10.  We must test all system functionality.
Summary of Project Deliverables
Project management-related deliverables: Team contract, Business Case, Work Breakdown Structure, Schedule, Gantt Chart, Cost baseline, Status Reports, Final Project Presentation, Lessons Learned Report and any other documents relating to the project.
Product-related deliverables:
1.    Integrated code upload system that allows users to look at a challenge, make an account 		upload a code submission. This system needs to be user friendly based on HCI studies and HCI 		standards to verify that this is done. The code submissions must be secure and there must be a 		scripting method that reads through code and grades it. 
2.     Submission system that allows customers to be able to upload their code under their own 		personal account. We will need to use PHP and have a database to store user information.
3.     A script that reads through user code and grades them. This will require at least two 			developers to work on this project at all times in order to be able to write scripts for each new 		challenge that comes out.
4.     A launched marketing campaign to let students know about the new system and the benefits of it. We will send out emails to listservs and we will contact all of the ICS student organizations to help us advertise this new system. We will also be making posters and we will pass out fliers on campus.
Project Success Criteria
The goal of this project is to finish this project withing our self alloted sixty day time frame and not go over our $500 dollar budget. We also want this system to be used continually by at 5% of the school population and 15% of the ICS student population. We want this system to be sustainable and be able to market it across other campuses around the nation.
